The paper deals with optimization questions related to selecting uniform point samples from metric spaces, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses lower bounds, hardness, and approximation hardness results, which are common topics in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of coresets for sampling uniform points from the Euclidean space suggests that the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the gap ratio measure, which is a measure of uniformity, suggesting that it may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
